Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COURTINGCOURTNEY settled near the back three wide around the first turn, advanced smartly three deep outside horses down the backstretch, rallied in the same path midway on the far turn to take control at the top of the lane and kept to the task late to hold safe at the finish. SILENT LUCIDITY took command on the rail into the first turn, relaxed behind the pacesetter on the fence down the back straight, started to move between foes in the three path turning for home, posed the only danger in upper stretch but could not threaten the winner at the wire. GRAND GIZMO threw his head on the break to have a poor start, went from three wide into the first turn to lead on the rail down the backside in an soft opening pace, continued to set the fractions on the far turn, was headed by the winner at the top of the stretch and finished up on the fence to hold for third at the end. ROCKLAND EXPRESS prompted the pace just outside early on, was content to track outside off the frontrunner with a half mile to run, was ridden between horses midpoint on the final turn, could not match strides with the closing runners on either side but still had enough left to save a minor placing in the end. SOCIAL JUSTICE trailed the field in the first turn, was unhurried at the back with a half mile remaining, began to find stride three wide at the quarter marker, angled six deep for the stretch run and passed weary foes in the stretch. I AM RESILIENT stalked near the rear in the two path down the back straight, was roused at the three eighths pole, made little impact and was not a factor running to the wire. KODIAK MAMBA (IRE) travelled on the rail in mid pack in the early stages of the race, made little impression inside through the far turn and was not involved to the drive to the finish line.

POPNFIZZ settled on the rail near the rear in hand behind foes into the turn, was shuffled inside to see the field into the stretch, could not really get interested in the drive to the wire, did not switch leads but was not that far beaten for third money at the finish.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOYA DE ORO took control after the first sixteenth, comfortably set the fractions on the turn, opened up on rivals when asked in mid stretch and kept on going to hold off rivals at the finish. LEGS LIKE FLATTER broke sharp to lead after the start, tracked the winner at the half mile marker, was hard ridden between foes two furlongs from the finish, looked to be the only threat running between horses at the top of the stretch and determinedly continued to chase the winner at the finish. MAGICAL TRICK had a good spot behind the top two down the backstretch on the rail, lost ground on the leaders throughout the turn, was roused for more run at the quarter pole and showed good late energy to close in and just win the nod capturing third. DIXIERIBSY stumbled soon after the break, recovered to track outside three wide in the third flight, advanced smartly around foes on the turn to be in the hunt five wide at the top of the lane and ran greenly through the stretch just missing holding onto third money at the finish line. SCORED was unhurried to trail the field outside down the backstretch, could not reach contention running on the turn and finished up evenly to the wire. IMPRESSIVE STYLE was urged between runners two deep in midfield at the half trying to keep position, could not make any headway on rivals running throughout the turn and retreated in upper stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 7 7F All Weather Track CR: 78. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 65900. INNER TURF FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD ONTARIO SIRED MAIDENS OR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD MAIDEN CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRUMLIN LAD was situated outside horses four deep down the backstretch, went around rivals four wide while in hand with three eighths to go, had a comfortable lead at the top of the lane and cruised home for an impressive victory. ONE TRUE GENTLEMAN tracked in mid pack with runners on either side with a half remaining, was shuffled back some in the turn, between foes was on hold at the quarter pole, had running room four wide with three sixteenths from home and closed well to be second best crossing the line. COLONEL MUSTARD settled in the middle of the pack in the beginning, waited inside behind the engaging foursome on the turn, was blocked behind horses at the top of the stretch, found room at the furlong pole and closed well to capture third money. AGILE DANCER trailed the field down the back straight, started to run angling outside at the quarter marker, shifted out pushing his way through to the six path turning for home and was one paced through the stretch to the finish. ROCK BULLET travelled near the back just off the fence down the backside, begun to rally outside horses at the two furlong pole, was floated out in the seven path for the drive and needed more late to be involved at the wire. MIAH SAID stalked at the back in the beginning, offered an early move boldly going around foes at the five sixteenth pole, was in with a chance five wide at the top of the lane and stalled in the final sixteenth. HUNGRY WOLF lead the field after the start, hounded the leader just sitting outside at the half mile marker, bid between runners for the top spot midpoint on the turn and weakened inside in mid stretch to not be a factor late. SOCIETY'S THUNDER prompted the pace three deep down the backside, poked his head in front battling with three others for the lead midway on the turn and tired in the three path in upper stretch. LEGS LIKE GIZMO pressed the pace inside at the start, took over the lead under a good hold on the fence at the half, battled inside for the front entering the turn, was swallowed up by many outside runners at the five sixteenths pole, lost his rail path in mid stretch, was steadied sharply and galloped to the finish.
